=== Set Tests ===
Set from [1,2,3,2,1,4,3]:
[1, 2, 3, 4]
After adding 4 and 2 (duplicate) to [1,2,3]:
[1, 2, 3, 4]
Set has 20: true
Set has 40: false
After removing 3 from [1,2,3,4,5]:
[1, 2, 4, 5]
Union of [1,2,3] and [3,4,5]:
[1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
Intersection of [1,2,3,4] and [3,4,5,6]:
[3, 4]
Difference [1,2,3,4] - [3,4,5]:
[1, 2]
String set from duplicates:
[apple, banana, cherry]
After adding 'date':
[apple, banana, cherry, date]
Empty set length: 0
After adding to empty set:
[first]
Set length: 5

=== Queue Tests ===
Empty queue is empty: true
Queue after enqueuing 3 items:
[first, second, third]
Dequeued item: a
Queue after dequeue:
[b, c]
Front of queue: 10
Queue still has: 3 items
Dequeue from empty returns: null
Peek empty queue: null
Queue with 1 item is empty: false
Queue after removing only item is empty: true
Queue created from array:
[100, 200, 300, 400]
Queue length: 6
FIFO: First out: A , Second out: B

=== Stack Tests ===
Empty stack is empty: true
Stack after pushing 3 items:
[bottom, middle, top]
Popped item: c
Stack after pop:
[a, b]
Top of stack: 30
Stack still has: 3 items
Pop from empty returns: null
Peek empty stack: null
Stack with 1 item is empty: false
Stack after removing only item is empty: true
Stack created from array:
[100, 200, 300, 400]
Stack length: 7
LIFO: First pop: C , Second pop: B

